 Barony of St. Trinian's in the Isle of Man |url=http://www.dgnhas.org.uk/tdgnhas/3027.pdf |journal=Transactions of the Dumfriesshire and Galloway Natural History and Antiquarian Society |volume=27 |pages=173\u2013182 |issn=0141-1292 |ref=ZZZM26 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Megaw |first1=RS |last2=Megaw |first2=EM |year=2013 |origyear=1950 |chapter=The Norse Heritage in the Isle of Man |editor1-last=Fox |editor1-first=C |editor1-link=Cyril Fox |editor2-last=Dickens |editor2-first=B |editor2-link=Bruce Dickins |title=The Early Cultures of North-West Europe |publisher=Cambridge University Press |location=Cambridge |isbn=978-1-107-68655-7 |pages=141\u2013170 |ref=ZZZM13 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Mills |first=AD |year=2003 |origyear=1991 |title=A Dictionary of British Place-Names |type=EPUB |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=Oxford |isbn=0-19-852758-6 |ref=ZZZM21 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Moore |first=D |year=2013 |origyear=2005 |title=The Welsh Wars of Independence |publisher=[[The History Press]] |location=Brimscombe Port |isbn=978-0-7524-9648-1 |ref=ZZZM5 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Muhr |first=K |year=2002 |chapter=Manx Place-Names: An Ulster View |chapter-url=https://www.ssns.org.uk/resources/Documents/Books/Man_2002/03_Muhr_Man_2002_pp_36-52.pdf |editor1-last=Davey |editor1-first=P |editor2-last=Finlayson |editor2-first=D |editor3-last=Thomlinson |editor3-first=P |title=Mannin Revisited: Twelve Essays on Manx Culture and Environment |publisher=The Scottish Society for Northern Studies |location=Edinburgh |pages=36\u201352 |isbn=0-9535226-2-8 |ref=ZZZM22 }}\n*{{cite ODNB |url=http://www.oxforddnb.com/view/article/54308 |title=Ross Family (per. c.1215\u2013c.1415) |last1=Munro |first1=R |last2=Munro |first2=J |year=2008 |edition=October 2008 |doi=10.1093/ref:odnb/54308 |isbn=9780198614111 |accessdate=5 July 2011 |url-access=subscription |ref=ZZZM25 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Murray |first=N |year=2005 |chapter=Swerving From the Path of Justice |editor-last=Oram |editor-first=