{"title_page": "Massachusetts Senate's 1st Bristol and Plymouth district", "text_new": "'''Massachusetts Senate's 1st Bristol and Plymouth district''' in the United States is one of 40 geographically-based [[legislative districts]] of the [[Massachusetts Senate]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sec.state.ma.us/ele/eledist/sen11idx.htm |title=Massachusetts Senatorial Districts |accessdate= April 8, 2020 |work=Sec.state.ma.us }}</ref> It covers portions of [[Bristol County, Massachusetts|Bristol]] and [[Plymouth County, Massachusetts|Plymouth]] counties.<ref name=2011ch152>{{citation |url=https://malegislature.gov/Laws/SessionLaws/Acts/2011/Chapter152 |accessdate= April 8, 2020 |work= Session Laws: Acts (2011) |title=An Act Establishing Executive Councillor and Senatorial Districts |quote=First Bristol and Plymouth }}</ref>  Since 2011 it is represented in the State Senate by [[Michael J. Rodrigues]] of the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]].<ref name=elections>{{cite web |accessdate= April 8, 2020 |work= Sec.state.ma.us |author= Commonwealth of Massachusetts, Elections Division |url= https://electionstats.state.ma.us/elections/search/year_from:1970/year_to:2020/office_id:9/district_id:58696 |title= State Senate elections: 1st Bristol and Plymouth district }}</ref>\n\n==Towns represented==\nThe district includes the following localities:<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20041023085644/http://www.mass.gov/legis/sendis03.htm |url= http://www.mass.gov/legis/sendis03.htm |title=Senatorial Districts |archivedate= October 23, 2004 |work= Mass.gov |quote=As established by Chapter 126, Section 3, of the Acts of 2001, based on the Federal census of 2000. See General Laws, Chapter 57 }}</ref><ref name=2011ch152 />\n* [[Fall River, Massachusetts|Fall River]]\n* [[Freetown, Massachusetts|Freetown]]\n* [[Lakeville, Massachusetts|Lakeville]]\n* [[Rochester, Massachusetts|Rochester]]\n* [[Somerset, Massachusetts|Somerset]]\n* [[Swansea, Massachusetts|Swansea]]\n* [[Westport, Massachusetts|Westport]]\n\n== List of senators ==\n* Marc R. Pacheco <ref>{{cite book |title=1997\u20131998 Public Officers of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts |year= |location= Boston |url=https://archive.org/stream/publicofficersof19971998bost |via=Internet Archive |chapter=Senate of the General Court of Massachusetts }}</ref>\n* Thomas C. Norton\n* [[Joan Menard]], 2000\u20132011 <ref name=elections />\n* Michael J. Rodrigues, 2011-current<ref name=elections />\n\n==See also==\n* [[List_of_elections_in_Massachusetts#Massachusetts_Senate|List of Massachusetts Senate elections]]\n* [[List of Massachusetts General Courts]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{Massachusetts Senate}}\n{{MassGenCourtDistricts}}\n{{Massachusetts government}}\n[[Category:Massachusetts General Court districts|Senate ]]\n[[Category:Government of Bristol County, Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:Government of Plymouth County, Massachusetts]]\n\n{{Massachusetts-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Massachusetts Senate's 1st Bristol and Plymouth district''' in the United States is one of 40 geographically-based [[legislative districts]] of the [[Massachusetts Senate]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sec.state.ma.us/ele/eledist/sen11idx.htm |title=Massachusetts Senatorial Districts |accessdate= April 8, 2020 |work=Sec.state.ma.us }}</ref> It covers portions of [[Bristol County, Massachusetts|Bristol]] and [[Plymouth County, Massachusetts|Plymouth]] counties.<ref name=2011ch152>{{citation |url=https://malegislature.gov/Laws/SessionLaws/Acts/2011/Chapter152 |accessdate= April 8, 2020 |work= Session Laws: Acts (2011) |title=An Act Establishing Executive Councillor and Senatorial Districts |quote=First Bristol and Plymouth }}</ref>  Since 2011 it is represented in the State Senate by [[Michael J. Rodrigues]] of the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]].<ref name=elections>{{cite web |accessdate= April 8, 2020 |work= Sec.state.ma.us |author= Commonwealth 